# DeWeb Design System — Creative Director Rules

## Stack (curated — do NOT add competing UI frameworks)

| Layer | Tool | Why |
|-------|------|-----|
| Components | **shadcn/ui** + **Radix UI** | Accessible primitives, Tailwind-native, zero runtime bloat |
| Motion (React) | **Framer Motion** | Page transitions, gestures, layout |
| Motion (DOM) | **Motion One** | Lightweight stagger / scroll micro-interactions |
| Scroll | **GSAP** + **Lenis** | Cinematic pinned scroll (home only) |
| 3D | **React Three Fiber** + **Drei** | Lazy-loaded hero scenes only |
| Styling | **Tailwind** + `dewebTokens` | Brand consistency |

### Do NOT install or use together
- **NextUI**, **Mantine** — conflicts with shadcn; doubles bundle size
- **Aceternity/Magic/Origin UI** as npm packages — copy patterns into `@/components/premium/` instead
- **Theatre.js**, **OGL**, **Spline** on every page — use only when a brief requires it; always lazy-load

## Visual identity
- Dark premium SaaS: `#05070a` bg, `#00f2ff` accent, glass panels, subtle purple/magenta mesh
- Reference quality: Apple clarity, Stripe trust, Linear motion, Framer polish
- Never: generic purple-gradient AI templates, stock card grids, flat Bootstrap layouts

## Motion rules
1. Respect `prefers-reduced-motion` — always use `useReducedMotion()`
2. No animation without purpose (conversion, orientation, delight)
3. Hero/cinematic: GSAP pin + Lenis on desktop only; mobile = stacked reveal
4. 3D: `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })` — never block LCP
5. Target: LCP < 2.5s, CLS < 0.1, INP < 200ms

## Component locations
- `@/components/ui/` — shadcn + core primitives (Button, Card, Badge)
- `@/components/premium/` — DeWeb signature effects (MagneticButton, SpotlightCard, BorderBeam, LazyScene3D)
- `@/lib/design-system/` — tokens, motion presets

## Every new section must define
- **Purpose** — what conversion goal it serves
- **Mobile layout** — designed first, not shrunk desktop
- **SEO** — semantic HTML, one h1 per page, no content in client-only canvas

## Implementation workflow
1. Audit existing section
2. Check `@/components/premium/` for reusable solution
3. Implement with tokens + motion presets
4. Test mobile + reduced motion
5. Run `npm run build` + `npm run lighthouse:audit` before deploy
